─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
Redistribution policy
─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

OpenPathAI does not redistribute any third-party model weights or source
code listed above. Users install these components at runtime from their
original sources (PyPI, Hugging Face, GitHub, Google Drive for
CTransPath). Redistribution terms remain the responsibility of those
sources.

Iron rule #12 of the project (see CLAUDE.md §2): import but never vendor
AGPL-licensed dependencies. The fallback resolvers in Phases 13 + 14
guarantee that the core library surface (`openpathai foundation`,
`openpathai detection`, `openpathai segmentation`) remains usable
without any AGPL import, at the cost of reduced capability (MIT-licensed
synthetic detectors / segmenters instead of production models).
